sequenceDiagram
    participant MM as ModelMesh Controller<br/>(modelmesh-serving)
    participant Puller as model-serving-puller<br/>8084/TCP gRPC
    participant Pullman as pullman Library
    participant Storage as Cloud Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Adapter as Runtime Adapter<br/>8085/TCP gRPC
    participant Runtime as Inference Runtime<br/>(Triton/MLServer/OVMS/TorchServe)

    Note over MM,Runtime: Flow 1: Model Load (standalone puller)

    MM->>Puller: gRPC LoadModel(modelId, modelKey)<br/>8084/TCP plaintext localhost
    Note right of Puller: Extract storage credentials<br/>from modelKey JSON
    Puller->>Pullman: Download model artifacts
    Pullman->>Storage: HTTPS GET model artifacts<br/>443/TCP TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Provider credentials
    Storage-->>Pullman: Model files (binary)
    Note right of Pullman: Write to /models/{modelId}/<br/>FNV-64a cache key for client reuse
    Pullman-->>Puller: Download complete
    Note right of Puller: Strip credentials from modelKey<br/>Rewrite path to local filesystem
    Puller->>Adapter: gRPC LoadModel(modelId, localPath)<br/>8085/TCP plaintext localhost
    Note right of Adapter: Create runtime-specific layout:<br/>Triton: config.pbtxt + symlinks<br/>MLServer: model-settings.json<br/>OVMS: JSON config + batch reload<br/>TorchServe: .mar symlink
    Adapter->>Runtime: Load model via runtime API<br/>gRPC or HTTP localhost
    Runtime-->>Adapter: Model loaded successfully
    Adapter-->>Puller: LoadModel response (size, maxConcurrency)
    Puller-->>MM: LoadModel response

    Note over MM,Runtime: Flow 2: Model Load (embedded puller)

    MM->>Adapter: gRPC LoadModel(modelId, modelKey)<br/>8085/TCP plaintext localhost
    Adapter->>Storage: HTTPS GET model artifacts<br/>443/TCP TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Provider credentials
    Storage-->>Adapter: Model files (binary)
    Adapter->>Runtime: Load model via runtime API<br/>localhost
    Runtime-->>Adapter: Model loaded
    Adapter-->>MM: LoadModel response

    Note over MM,Runtime: Flow 3: Model Unload

    MM->>Puller: gRPC UnloadModel(modelId)<br/>8084/TCP plaintext localhost
    Puller->>Adapter: gRPC UnloadModel(modelId)<br/>8085/TCP plaintext localhost
    Adapter->>Runtime: Unload model via runtime API<br/>localhost
    Runtime-->>Adapter: Model unloaded
    Adapter-->>Puller: UnloadModel response
    Note right of Puller: Delete local model files<br/>from /models/{modelId}/
    Puller-->>MM: UnloadModel response

    Note over Adapter,Runtime: Flow 4: Keras-to-TF Conversion (Triton only)

    Note right of Adapter: Detect .h5 Keras model file
    Adapter->>Adapter: subprocess exec<br/>/opt/scripts/tf_pb.py
    Note right of Adapter: Python reads .h5 file<br/>TensorFlow exports SavedModel<br/>to local filesystem
